The paper deals with a machine learning problem of multi-label classification, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed approach involves exploiting label correlations, which is also a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve real-world datasets related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), indicating that the paper may also belong to these subfields. Finally, the paper deals with incomplete label assignments, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR).
